<subSubSection id="D47E054205491484ED717F908E13D4BD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="0B2F92335E3924EE409DFA330C1163D2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B40E159EC4B67F0F086F16B828C00F98" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Slender twining annual herb, stems glabrous. Leaves petiolate, 3-9 
<normalizedToken id="49E426787E0F96FF89777AC5E3D2907A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-9 cm in outline but usually small, palmately divided into 3 lobes, shallowly cordate to truncate and briefly cuneate onto petiole, the terminal lobe lanceolate acuminate, narrowed at base, the 2 lateral lobes forked or trifurcate, glabrous, both surfaces green. Inflorescence of few-flowered pedunculate cymes, flowers often solitary; peduncles 1.5-5 cm, recurving in fruit; bracteoles 2 mm, linear-lanceolate, scarious with green midrib; pedicels 6-15 mm, lateral flowers often developing tardily; sepals subequal, 9-12(-15) 
<normalizedToken id="06A96B6FFEE588E28295BC526C8595BE" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3 mm, linear-lanceolate, acuminate, densely covered in stiff bristles c. 3 mm long; corolla 1.6-2.3 cm long, the tube white, glabrous, the limb bluish-purple, c. 2 cm diam., unlobed but midpetaline bands terminating in a tooth. Capsules subglobose 9 
<normalizedToken id="4F0B7457BCF5E799E07BDF45AC0612EB" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
10 mm, glabrous; seeds up to 6.5 
<normalizedToken id="059FE661A134DDC3F3CF1B0BDAE1FF40" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.5 mm, appressed pubescent often appearing glabrous, brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8D86E9FF8332294FC49DFFEADA36D03B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="variation">
